BACKGROUND: To determine if the more interventionist approach of screening with 
the tuberculin test and chemoprophylaxis for high-risk positive reactors to 
control tuberculosis in long-term care facilities is cost-effective when 
compared to the case-finding and treatment approach.
METHOD: A decision-analysis model was designed wherein systematic screening with 
