BACKGROUND: The optimal method of coronary revascularization in dialysis 
patients is controversial, as previous small retrospective studies have reported 
increased cardiac events after percutaneous transluminal coronary angioplasty 
(PTCA) compared with coronary artery bypass (CAB) surgery. The purpose of this 
